cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CL

The paper discusses a new RSS feed ranking method that uses information retrieval techniques and user profiles to recommend information to users based on their past choices. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Computation and Language (cs.CL). However, given the focus on information retrieval and user profiles, cs.IR is the most likely category.
